article.description: North Carolina A&T 91, Morgan St. 79 OT
article.headline: North Carolina A&T 91, Morgan St. 79 OT
article.linkText: North Carolina A&T 91, Morgan St. 79 OT
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Steven Rush scored a game-high 26 points to help North Carolina A&T defeat Morgan State in overtime 91-79 on Monday night. Austin Ewing added 17 points, while Jason Wills had a double-double with 13 points and 14 rebounds for the Aggies (12-15, 8-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Glenn Nelson chipped in 12 points. Morgan State (10-15, 8-6 MEAC) was ahead 38-35 at the break and the lead changed 11 times in the game, but North Carolina A&T outpaced Morgan State in overtime 22-10. The Aggies hit 90.9 percent from the free throw line in overtime, hitting 10-of-11 to Morgan State's 0-of-2. Ronald Timus led Morgan State with 20 points, while Reggie Holmes scored 18 points and Joseph McLean added 17 points.
